text: Lyudmila Mokhnacheva also written as Ljudmila Mokhnatsjeva and Ljudmila Mokhnatsjeva (Russian: Людмила Мохначева, born 1944) is a Soviet former long track speed skater, who was active in the 1960s and 1970s. Mokhnatsjeva represented her nation at the World Allround Speed Skating Championships for Women in 1969, finishing 5th overall. She participated also at the European Speed Skating Championships for Women in 1970. She also competed at other international competitions. At the 1970 Soviet Allround Championships she won the bronze medal. == Records== === Personal records === ==References== Category:1944 births Category:Place of birth missing (living people) Category:Date of birth missing (living people) Category:Soviet female speed skaters Category:Living people
